WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:19.000
Cheetah presents Hamlet Prince of Denmark by William Shakespeare.

00:30.000 --> 00:40.000
One. The Ghost.

00:40.000 --> 00:51.000
One night at Elsinore Castle in Denmark, two guards see a ghost.

00:51.000 --> 00:54.000
It looks like King Hamlet.

00:54.000 --> 00:59.000
But it can't be. King Hamlet is dead.

00:59.000 --> 01:12.000
We must tell Horatio Prince Hamlet's friend. Perhaps the Ghost wants to give a message to the Prince.

01:12.000 --> 01:20.000
The next night Horatio stays to watch with the guards. The Ghost appears again.

01:20.000 --> 01:26.000
It is wearing the same armour as the Old King.

01:26.000 --> 01:30.000
What do you want? Speak to us.

01:30.000 --> 01:39.000
It refuses to speak. I shall tell the Prince. Perhaps the Ghost will speak to him.

01:39.000 --> 01:47.000
This is a bad sign. Something sinister is happening in Denmark.

01:47.000 --> 01:53.000
Prince Hamlet is very sad. His father the king is dead.

01:53.000 --> 02:02.000
Gertrude his mother has married Claudius his father's brother. Claudius has become the new king.

02:02.000 --> 02:15.000
Hamlet does not like his uncle. It is time to think about the future. I shall be a father to you and you will be king after me Hamlet.

02:15.000 --> 02:23.000
Stay here with us. Do not go back to university. We love you Hamlet.

02:23.000 --> 02:36.000
I shall obey you, madam. My father was a better man than Claudius. My mother was weak and foolish to marry my uncle.

02:36.000 --> 02:45.000
Horatio comes to tell Hamlet about the Ghost. Horatio has studied for many years with the Prince at university.

02:45.000 --> 02:52.000
He is Hamlet's best friend and the Prince trusts him completely.

02:52.000 --> 03:02.000
I hate this place, Horatio. My uncle and my mother are so happy. How can they forget my father so soon?

03:02.000 --> 03:10.000
My lord, I saw your father last night. What do you mean?

03:10.000 --> 03:19.000
Come to the castle walls at midnight of the cliff. Then you'll understand.

03:19.000 --> 03:25.000
Hamlet sees the Ghost of his father. It signals him to follow.

03:25.000 --> 03:34.000
I am your father's spirit. If you ever loved me, revenge my murder.

03:34.000 --> 03:36.000
Murder?

03:36.000 --> 03:53.000
My wife Gertrude was unfaithful to me. My brother Claudius murdered me. While I was sleeping in my garden, he poured poison in my ear.

03:54.000 --> 04:01.000
The sun is rising. I must go. Hamlet, remember me.

04:01.000 --> 04:08.000
Hamlet does not know what to do. Perhaps the Ghost is telling lies.

04:08.000 --> 04:17.000
I shall pretend to be mad. Nobody will pay attention to a poor, crazy prince.

04:17.000 --> 04:27.000
I shall investigate my father's death. If the Ghost's story is true, I shall kill my uncle.

04:48.000 --> 05:01.000
So Hamlet, who was very intelligent, began to play the part of a madman. He did strange things, and he talked in a crazy way.

05:01.000 --> 05:14.000
He often said things with a hidden meaning, which only he understood. The people believed that Hamlet was mad, and they hoped that he would soon get better.

05:15.000 --> 05:28.000
The Queen was very worried, because she loved her son. Only Horatio and the Gods knew the secret of Hamlet's meeting with the Ghost.

05:28.000 --> 05:42.000
2. Hamlet and Ophelia

05:42.000 --> 05:53.000
Ophelia lives at the castle. She has a brother, Laertes, who is studying in Paris. Ophelia is in love with Hamlet.

05:54.000 --> 06:07.000
One day while she is sowing, Hamlet comes to her room. Later she tells her father, Polonius, a foolish old Lord, about Hamlet's visit.

06:08.000 --> 06:23.000
He looked so sad. He was only half-dressed. He stared at me, and then he left without saying a word.

06:23.000 --> 06:27.000
Is he mad for your love?

06:27.000 --> 06:32.000
I don't know, but I think so.

06:32.000 --> 06:36.000
I must tell the King and Queen.

06:36.000 --> 06:47.000
Polonius trusts Claudius in Gertrude. He has no idea that Claudius is a murderer, or that Gertrude has been unfaithful to King Hamlet.

06:47.000 --> 06:57.000
Hamlet's love for my daughter has made him mad. That is possible. But how can we know for certain?

06:57.000 --> 07:11.000
We shall hide while Hamlet and Ophelia are talking. We shall listen to their conversation and discover the truth. You will see that I am right.

07:11.000 --> 07:21.000
Polonius gives instructions to Ophelia. He wants her to walk up and down the castle hall, reading her prayer book.

07:21.000 --> 07:28.000
Ophelia, you must help us find out the truth about Prince Hamlet's madness.

07:28.000 --> 07:31.000
I shall obey you, Father.

07:31.000 --> 07:36.000
Quickly, here he comes. Pretend that you are reading.

07:36.000 --> 07:49.000
Hamlet is thinking deeply. He wants to escape from his problems by committing suicide. His mind is full of questions.

07:49.000 --> 07:58.000
To be or not to be. That is the question.

07:58.000 --> 08:12.000
Is it better to live or die? But what happens after we die? Nobody knows.

08:12.000 --> 08:23.000
I am stupid. I must stop thinking and do something. I must discover the truth.

08:23.000 --> 08:35.000
But look, here comes Ophelia. Why is she standing there? Is it a trap?

08:35.000 --> 08:44.000
The prince is angry with Ophelia because he realizes that she is a spy for her father Polonius and King Claudius.

08:44.000 --> 08:47.000
I loved you once.

08:47.000 --> 08:50.000
I believed so.

08:50.000 --> 09:02.000
No, I never loved you. All women are stupid. They paint their faces and talk foolishly.

09:02.000 --> 09:09.000
Nobody should get married. Go away to a nunnery.

09:09.000 --> 09:18.000
The king does not believe that love is the reason for Hamlet's madness. He is very suspicious.

09:18.000 --> 09:29.000
Perhaps Hamlet knows my secret. We must watch him carefully. It is dangerous when a prince is mad.

09:29.000 --> 09:40.000
Poor Hamlet. Everybody admired him before. He was the perfect prince.

09:40.000 --> 09:50.000
Now his mind is ruined. Help him sweet heavens.

09:59.000 --> 10:03.000
Hamlet enjoyed making fun of Polonius.

10:03.000 --> 10:11.000
One day the prince was reading a book when he met the foolish old lord.

10:11.000 --> 10:14.000
What are you reading?

10:14.000 --> 10:23.000
Words. Words. Words. But what is the book about? It's full of lies.

10:23.000 --> 10:31.000
The writer says that old men are foolish, weak and have grey hair.

10:31.000 --> 10:34.000
Can you see that cloud Polonius?

10:34.000 --> 10:38.000
Yes, my lord. It looks like a camel, doesn't it?

10:38.000 --> 10:40.000
Yes, my lord.

10:40.000 --> 10:44.000
No. I think it looks like a weasel.

10:44.000 --> 10:47.000
Yes, my lord.

10:47.000 --> 10:51.000
Good-bye, you foolish old man.

10:51.000 --> 10:55.000
Three. The play.

10:55.000 --> 11:02.000
Two university friends come to visit Hamlet. Their names are Rosencrantz and Gildenstern.

11:02.000 --> 11:12.000
The name of the king of the king of the king of the king of the king of the king of the king of the king.

11:12.000 --> 11:18.000
They come to see Hamlet. Their names are Rosencrantz and Gildenstern.

11:18.000 --> 11:27.000
At first Hamlet is very pleased to see them, but they ask a lot of questions and he becomes suspicious.

11:27.000 --> 11:32.000
Why are you behaving so strangely?

11:32.000 --> 11:34.000
What's the matter with you?

11:34.000 --> 11:39.000
Tell us what you are thinking about. We are your friends.

11:39.000 --> 11:46.000
I think the king has sent them. They are spying on me.

11:46.000 --> 11:50.000
I shall not tell them anything.

11:50.000 --> 11:55.000
I cannot trust anyone except Horatio.

11:55.000 --> 12:07.000
Some travelling actors arrive at Elsinor. Hamlet loves the theatre and he greets them like old friends.

12:07.000 --> 12:11.000
Welcome to Elsinor.

12:11.000 --> 12:15.000
We have come to perform a play for the king and queen.

12:15.000 --> 12:19.000
That gives me an idea, Horatio.

12:19.000 --> 12:24.000
I shall put some extra words in their play.

12:24.000 --> 12:31.000
I shall put the ghost's story on the stage.

12:31.000 --> 12:47.000
That night, glorious and gertrude watch the play. There are three characters, the player king, the player queen, and Lucianus, the queen's lover, the murderer.

12:47.000 --> 12:51.000
I shall always love you.

12:51.000 --> 12:55.000
But if I die, you will marry again.

12:55.000 --> 12:59.000
No, never.

12:59.000 --> 13:05.000
Do you like the play, Mother? The lady speaks too much about love.

13:05.000 --> 13:16.000
All the court of Denmark watch the play. Ophelia, Poludius, Horatio, Rosenkranz and Gildenstern are all there.

13:16.000 --> 13:25.000
But nobody knows the secret of King Hamlet's death, except Claudius and Hamlet.

13:26.000 --> 13:34.000
On the stage, while the player king is sleeping, the murderer pours poison in his ear.

13:34.000 --> 13:39.000
Hamlet watches Claudius' face carefully.

13:39.000 --> 13:43.000
This is the ghost's story.

13:43.000 --> 13:50.000
If Claudius is afraid, I shall know he is guilty.

13:50.000 --> 13:57.000
Suddenly, Claudius stands up and runs out of the court. Everybody follows him.

13:57.000 --> 14:02.000
The actors do not know what the problem is.

14:02.000 --> 14:05.000
Lights, lights, stop the play.

14:05.000 --> 14:13.000
Did you see that, Horatio? The king is frightened. The ghost's story is true.

14:14.000 --> 14:20.000
After the play, Claudius feels very guilty, so he goes to pray in the chapel.

14:20.000 --> 14:23.000
Hamlet finds him there.

14:23.000 --> 14:28.000
I want God to forgive me for my brother's murder.

14:28.000 --> 14:32.000
Perhaps, if I pray, he will help me.

14:32.000 --> 14:37.000
It would be easy for me to kill him now.

14:37.000 --> 14:44.000
But if I kill him while he is praying, his soul will go to heaven.

14:44.000 --> 14:48.000
I want him to go to hell.

14:48.000 --> 14:52.000
I shall wait for another opportunity.

14:52.000 --> 14:59.000
I cannot repent. God doesn't listen to my words.

15:07.000 --> 15:10.000
It's good to see you again, my friends.

15:10.000 --> 15:15.000
Let me give you some advice for the play tonight.

15:15.000 --> 15:21.000
First of all, you shouldn't speak too loudly or too quietly.

15:21.000 --> 15:26.000
If the audience can't hear you, they won't be pleased.

15:26.000 --> 15:31.000
But if you shout, they won't like it.

15:31.000 --> 15:36.000
Secondly, you shouldn't move your hands too much.

15:36.000 --> 15:43.000
But it's important to speak clearly, so the audience will understand you.

15:43.000 --> 15:49.000
Next, remember to pay attention to the meaning of the words.

15:49.000 --> 15:59.000
Last of all, don't add any extra lines to the play, and don't change the writer's words.

15:59.000 --> 16:04.000
I'll repeat all that because it's important.

16:04.000 --> 16:10.000
First of all, don't speak too loudly or too quietly.

16:10.000 --> 16:15.000
Secondly, don't move your hands too much.

16:15.000 --> 16:19.000
Thirdly, you should speak clearly.

16:19.000 --> 16:25.000
Next, you should pay attention to the meaning of the words.

16:25.000 --> 16:33.000
Finally, don't add any extra lines or change the words of the play.

16:34.000 --> 16:48.000
For murder and exile

16:48.000 --> 16:54.000
It is the middle of the night, the time for witches and ghosts.

16:54.000 --> 16:57.000
Hamlet goes to see his mother in her bedroom.

16:57.000 --> 17:03.000
He does not know that someone is hiding behind the curtain and listening to everything.

17:03.000 --> 17:10.000
Hamlet, why did you offend the king?

17:10.000 --> 17:15.000
Mother, why did you betray my father?

17:15.000 --> 17:20.000
Don't move. I want to talk to you.

17:20.000 --> 17:26.000
I want to make you look into the mirror of your soul.

17:26.000 --> 17:32.000
The queen is afraid of Hamlet, and she begins to scream.

17:32.000 --> 17:36.000
The spy behind the curtain shouts for help.

17:36.000 --> 17:43.000
Hamlet turns round quickly, and without thinking, kills the listener.

17:43.000 --> 17:49.000
Are you going to murder me? Help! Help!

17:49.000 --> 17:55.000
What's that? Is it a rat? Is it the king?

17:56.000 --> 18:05.000
When Hamlet pulls back the curtain, he sees Polonius. Dead.

18:05.000 --> 18:12.000
What have you done? You have murdered Polonius.

18:12.000 --> 18:20.000
I thought it was the king. I'm sorry that I have killed this poor fool.

18:21.000 --> 18:30.000
But mother, I'm not as bad as you. You killed a king and married his brother.

18:30.000 --> 18:33.000
What do you mean?

18:33.000 --> 18:43.000
Suddenly the ghost appears in the room. He has come to remind Hamlet to take revenge before it is too late.

18:43.000 --> 18:51.000
Gertrude cannot see or hear him, so she thinks that Hamlet is crazy.

18:51.000 --> 19:03.000
Hamlet, don't hurt your mother. Remember that you must kill Claudius. Don't waste time.

19:04.000 --> 19:13.000
What is he looking at? He's mad. Oh, my poor son.

19:13.000 --> 19:25.000
Can't you see him, mother? Don't you pity him? Hamlet, there is nothing there except the air.

19:25.000 --> 19:29.000
The ghost disappears.

19:29.000 --> 19:41.000
No, I'm not mad, mother. Look at this portrait of my father. He was a good, brave, handsome man.

19:41.000 --> 19:47.000
Remember him and stay away from Claudius.

19:47.000 --> 19:51.000
I will, sweet Hamlet.

19:51.000 --> 19:58.000
But as soon as Claudius kisses you, you will forget everything and tell him my secrets.

19:58.000 --> 20:03.000
No. I promise not to betray you.

20:03.000 --> 20:14.000
I am glad, mother. Now I must take away Polonius' body. Good night.

20:14.000 --> 20:22.000
When Claudius hears that Hamlet has killed Polonius, he decides to send the prince away.

20:22.000 --> 20:31.000
Hamlet is dangerous. I shall send him to England. Perhaps he will recover from his madness in a different country.

20:32.000 --> 20:41.000
Rosen, Cranston, Guildenstern, go with him and look after him.

20:41.000 --> 20:53.000
I shall send secret letters to the king of England. I shall tell the English to execute Hamlet as soon as he arrives.

20:53.000 --> 20:58.000
When he is dead, I shall be safe.

21:02.000 --> 21:09.000
It was a long journey by sea to England.

21:09.000 --> 21:16.000
One night, Hamlet could not sleep because he was thinking about all his problems.

21:16.000 --> 21:21.000
He got out of bed and walked around the ship.

21:21.000 --> 21:30.000
While Rosengrants and Guildenstern were sleeping, he stole Claudius' letter to the king of England.

21:31.000 --> 21:37.000
To his surprise, he read these orders.

21:37.000 --> 21:43.000
As soon as Hamlet arrives, cut off his head!

21:43.000 --> 21:47.000
Hamlet quickly prepared another letter.

21:47.000 --> 21:54.000
Execute the people who bring you this letter, he wrote. He signed it.

21:54.000 --> 21:57.000
Claudius.

21:57.000 --> 22:02.000
Then he went back to his cabin and hid the original letter.

22:02.000 --> 22:11.000
When Rosencrants and Guildenstern arrive in England, he thought, the English king will execute them.

22:11.000 --> 22:16.000
But how am I going to return to Denmark?

22:16.000 --> 22:26.000
The next morning, Rosencrants and Guildenstern woke up without realizing that the letter had been changed.

22:28.000 --> 22:39.000
5. Suicide

22:39.000 --> 22:45.000
Polunius' son Leoty's returns to Denmark from Paris.

22:45.000 --> 22:48.000
He is very angry.

22:48.000 --> 22:52.000
Claudius, you have killed my father.

22:52.000 --> 22:59.000
I shall persuade the people to rebel against you. There will be a revolution.

22:59.000 --> 23:04.000
No, Leoty's. Hamlet is responsible for everything.

23:04.000 --> 23:09.000
But how did my father die? Why is it a secret?

23:09.000 --> 23:16.000
Be patient. When I have explained everything, you will understand.

23:16.000 --> 23:19.000
I am your friend.

23:19.000 --> 23:29.000
Ophelia comes to see Leoty's. She loved Hamlet, but he killed her father. This has made her mad.

23:29.000 --> 23:35.000
She sings sad songs and gives flowers to everyone she meets.

23:35.000 --> 23:39.000
What is the matter with my sister?

23:39.000 --> 23:44.000
She has lost her mind, poor girl.

23:44.000 --> 23:53.000
He is dead, lady. He is dead.

23:53.000 --> 24:00.000
It will never come again.

24:00.000 --> 24:07.000
His bid was as white as snow.

24:07.000 --> 24:16.000
He is gone. He is gone.

24:16.000 --> 24:23.000
Love remember me.

24:23.000 --> 24:27.000
Do you see this?

24:27.000 --> 24:31.000
Oh God!

24:31.000 --> 24:34.000
A sailor brings a letter to Horatio.

24:34.000 --> 24:39.000
When he opens it, he discovers that it is from Hamlet.

24:39.000 --> 24:46.000
Horatio, I am in Denmark. Some pirates attacked our ship.

24:46.000 --> 24:54.000
While everybody was fighting, I jumped onto their ship. I paid them, and they brought me home to Denmark.

24:54.000 --> 25:02.000
Rosenkrantz and Guildenstern have continued to England. I shall tell you more about them when I see you.

25:02.000 --> 25:07.000
Meet me in the graveyard. Hamlet.

25:07.000 --> 25:14.000
I shall go to him immediately. I am glad he is safe.

25:14.000 --> 25:22.000
Claudius also receives a letter from Hamlet. He has a private conversation with Leoty's.

25:22.000 --> 25:31.000
But why didn't you put Hamlet in prison? He is very popular with the people. It was impossible to punish him.

25:31.000 --> 25:40.000
The best thing was to send him to England. He has killed my father and driven my sister out of her mind.

25:40.000 --> 25:53.000
I would do anything to get my revenge. This letter is from Hamlet. He is back in Denmark. I am glad. I will kill him.

25:53.000 --> 26:00.000
I have a better plan. The Queen comes in.

26:00.000 --> 26:20.000
I have bad news, Leoty's. Ophelia is dead. She wanted to put flowers on the willow tree. While she was climbing, she slipped and fell into the river.

26:20.000 --> 26:28.000
She floated there, singing. Then she drowned.

26:28.000 --> 26:32.000
Was it suicide?

26:32.000 --> 26:46.000
Nobody knows. Perhaps it was an accident. Oh, sweet Ophelia. I hoped she would marry Hamlet.

26:46.000 --> 26:51.000
Come. Let us go and bury her.

26:51.000 --> 26:57.000
Now Hamlet has killed my father and my sister.

26:57.000 --> 27:10.000
Hamlet meets Horatio in the graveyard. They see a grave digger. He is preparing a new grave and he has uncovered some old bones.

27:10.000 --> 27:14.000
Hamlet begins to talk about death.

27:14.000 --> 27:29.000
Look at this skull, Horatio. It is Yoricks. He was the court jester. Alas, poor Yorick. I knew him, Horatio.

27:29.000 --> 27:37.000
When I was a child, he carried me on his back. His jokes were the best.

27:37.000 --> 27:42.000
He cannot make anybody laugh now.

27:42.000 --> 27:52.000
Perhaps this skull belonged to a beautiful lady. She cannot paint her face now.

27:52.000 --> 28:02.000
Perhaps this skull belonged to a lawyer. He cannot show how clever he is now.

28:02.000 --> 28:15.000
Perhaps this skull belonged to a court gentleman. He cannot wear elegant clothes now.

28:15.000 --> 28:34.000
There is a willow by the river. Its silver leaves shine in the glassy water. Ophelia walked there,

28:34.000 --> 28:41.000
picking the flowers to hang on the graceful branches of the tree.

28:41.000 --> 28:55.000
But as she was climbing up to the sky, a thin branch broke under her small feet and she fell down into the weeping brook.

28:55.000 --> 29:07.000
Her dress spread wide and, like a mermaid, she floated on the surface, singing old melodies.

29:07.000 --> 29:21.000
She was as happy as a creature of the water, but as her clothes grew heavy, they pulled her down to the dark bottom of the river,

29:22.000 --> 29:25.000
to muddy death.

29:34.000 --> 29:40.000
6. The rest is silence.

29:40.000 --> 29:50.000
While he is standing in the graveyard, Hamlet sees a procession approaching. It is Ophelia's funeral.

29:50.000 --> 29:54.000
The queen throws flowers into the grave and says,

29:54.000 --> 30:07.000
Sweet to the sweet. Hamlet did not know that Ophelia was dead. He is shocked. He jumps into the grave and fights with Laertes.

30:07.000 --> 30:17.000
You killed my father and my sister. I loved Ophelia more than 40,000 brothers.

30:17.000 --> 30:25.000
Laertes wants his revenge. He and Claudius decide how to kill Hamlet.

30:25.000 --> 30:33.000
You must challenge Hamlet to a fencing match. He loves this sport. He will certainly agree.

30:33.000 --> 30:43.000
Yes, and I shall put poison on the tip of my sword. If I cut him, he will die.

30:43.000 --> 30:53.000
And if this plan fails, I shall give Hamlet a poisoned drink. Hamlet accepts the challenge.

30:53.000 --> 31:03.000
He does not know about the poisoned sword. To him, the fight is just sport, something he enjoys.

31:03.000 --> 31:11.000
I am sorry for your father's death, Laertes. I accept your apology, Hamlet.

31:11.000 --> 31:15.000
Now, let's begin the fight.

31:15.000 --> 31:27.000
Here is a drink for you, Hamlet. If you're thirsty, good luck to you. I have bet six horses that you will win.

31:27.000 --> 31:37.000
Hamlet fights well and scores the first points. The queen is very happy. She picks up the cup of poison.

31:37.000 --> 31:46.000
Claudius tries to stop her drinking, but it is too late. No, go through to do not drink.

31:46.000 --> 31:49.000
I drink to Hamlet.

31:54.000 --> 32:05.000
Laertes wounds Hamlet with the poisoned sword. Later in the confusion, they exchange swords, and Hamlet wounds Laertes.

32:06.000 --> 32:19.000
The poison enters their blood. Suddenly, the queen screams in pain. Laertes falls to the ground, and Hamlet begins to feel weak.

32:19.000 --> 32:23.000
The poison is working.

32:23.000 --> 32:25.000
Help me. I am dying.

32:25.000 --> 32:33.000
We are all going to die. The sword and the drink were poisoned. The king is to blame.

32:33.000 --> 32:42.000
Then, before I die, I shall have my revenge. This is for my father's murder.

32:42.000 --> 32:47.000
Treason! Treason!

32:47.000 --> 32:55.000
Hamlet is dying. Polunius, Ophelia, Laertes, Gertrude and Claudius are all dead.

32:55.000 --> 33:00.000
It is time for a new beginning in Denmark.

33:00.000 --> 33:03.000
I shall kill myself too.

33:03.000 --> 33:16.000
No, Horatio. You must live. Tell the truth to the world after I am dead. Tell my story.

33:16.000 --> 33:26.000
Good night, sweet prince, and flights of angels sing thee to thy rest.

34:00.000 --> 34:04.000
Frailty thy name is woman.

34:04.000 --> 34:09.000
Something is rotten in the state of Denmark.

34:09.000 --> 34:19.000
Adieu. Adieu. Adieu. Remember me.

34:19.000 --> 34:28.000
One may smile and smile and be a villain.

34:29.000 --> 34:37.000
The play is the thing wherein I'll catch the conscience of the king.

34:37.000 --> 34:46.000
To be or not to be. That is the question.

34:46.000 --> 34:52.000
Madness in great ones must not unwatched go.

34:52.000 --> 34:59.000
Suit the action to the word, the word to the action.

34:59.000 --> 35:05.000
My words fly up. My thoughts remain below.

35:05.000 --> 35:11.000
Words without thoughts never to heaven go.

35:11.000 --> 35:18.000
How now? A rat? Dead for a ducate? Dead?

35:18.000 --> 35:24.000
Thou turned my eyes into my very soul.

35:24.000 --> 35:30.000
